SIMPLE: eschew
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eschew
<hw>Es*chew"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Eshewed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Eshewing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF. <ets>eschever</ets>,
<ets>eschiver</ets>, <ets>eskiver</ets>, F. <ets>esquiver</ets>, fr.
OHG. <ets>sciuhen</ets>, G. <ets>scheuen</ets>; akin to E.
<ets>sky</ets>. See <er>Shy</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To shun; to avoid, as something wrong, or from a feeling of
distaste; to keep one's self clear of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They must not only <qex>eschew</qex> evil, but do good.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Beveridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To escape from; to avoid.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He who obeys, destruction shall <qex>eschew</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sandys.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eschewer</ent>⟦br⟧
